        Composed of the characters for "longevity" and "governor". Even
        such a quintessentially Japanese concept as sushi is spelled with
        ateji. Sushi came to be in the early Edo era (~1600s) and while
        the actual word indicates essentially means "vinegared" (referring
        to how the rice is treated), it was spelled with ateji instead.
    </div>
    </div>
    <div class="example-grid-container border-item">
    <div class="kanji-grid-area">独逸</div>
    <div class="thin row-grid-area">Meaning</div>
