    <div class="thin row-grid-area">Reading</div>
    <div class="thick row-grid-area">Doitsu</div>
    <div class="thin row-grid-area">Origin</div>
    <div class="thick row-grid-area last-area">Loanword</div>
    <div class="explanation-grid-area">
        Composed of the characters for "alone" and "deviate". The Japanese
        came into contact with the Western World relatively late, in the
        1800s. In this period, assigning ateji to foreign loanwords was
        still in vogue, and as such, many prominent countries in the West
        are known by their ateji in Japanese.
    </div>
    </div>
